## Problem to solve

Currently, any network errors within the Gitlab Migration (BulkImports) fail the import or the pipeline that raised the error, but some errors should trigger a retry instead of failing the import/pipeline.

Related to: https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/43155#note_421147461

## Proposed Solution

1. Create a `BulkImports::RetriableNetworkError`;
1. Rescue network errors like 502, 429, etc on `BulkImports::Clients::Graphql#execute` and `BulkImports::Gitlab::HTTP#request` and re-raise as `BulkImports::RetriableNetworkError`;
1. Rescue `BulkImports::RetriableNetworkError` on `BulkImports::PipelineWorker::#perform` and reschedule a job for the same worker;
1. The `BulkImports::PipelineWorker::#perform` should not retry more then 3 times.

### Summary

When accessing snippets through GraphQL, I want to access unaltered text content of the snippet blob the same way as I can through the [REST endpoint](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/api/project_snippets.html#snippet-repository-file-content)

### Steps to reproduce

1. Go to https://gitlab.com/-/graphql-explorer
1. Enter the following query
    ```
    {
      snippets(ids: "gid://gitlab/ProjectSnippet/1962251"){
        nodes {
          title
          webUrl
          blobs {
            nodes {
              name
              plainData
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
    ```

### Example Project

https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitter/webapp/-/snippets

